{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% set nav = 'treaty' %}

{% block title %}Our language: loss and revival · The Treaty · Robinson Huron Treaty{% endblock %}
{% block description %}Where Anishinaabemowin stands across the Robinson Huron Treaty territory, and the 21 nations' shared work to bring it back, funded by interest from the annuities settlement.{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}Anishinaabemowin in RHT territory: the 2021 speaker figures, and the 21-nation reclamation strategy funded by settlement interest. The flagship positive story from the settlement.{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}
<style>
  .lex { margin: 8px 0 4px; max-width: 44rem; }
  .lex__label { display: block; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--magenta); margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .lex__row { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .lex__row input {
    flex: 1; min-width: 12rem; padding: 13px 16px; font-size: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); border-radius: 999px; background: #fff; color: var(--ink);
  }
  .lex__row input:focus { outline: 3px solid var(--violet); outline-offset: 1px; border-color: var(--indigo); }
  .lex__row button {
    flex: none; border: none; background: var(--indigo); color: #fff; font-weight: 600; font-size: 16px;
    padding: 13px 24px; border-radius: 999px; cursor: pointer;
  }
  .lex__row button:hover { background: var(--indigo-deep); }
  .lex__note { margin: 8px 0 0; font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-3); }
  .lex-entry { margin: 18px 0 0; border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-left: 4px solid var(--magenta); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px 20px; background: #fff; }
  .lex-entry__word { margin: 0; font-family: var(--serif, var(--sans)); font-size: 22px; color: var(--indigo-deep); }
  .lex-entry__def { margin: 6px 0 10px; font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink); }
  .lex-entry__meta { margin: 0; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink-2); }
  .lex-entry__meta dt { font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink-3); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.03em; font-size: 11px; margin-top: 8px; }
  .lex-entry__meta dd { margin: 2px 0 0; }
  .lex-usage { margin: 18px 0 0; font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-3); }
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block hero %}
<section class="hero">
  <div class="wrap wrap--wide">
    <p class="eyebrow">The Treaty · our language</p>
    <h1>Our language: loss and revival.</h1>
    <p class="lead">The treaty is more than land and money. It is also the language that carries who we are. Anishinaabemowin, in our own Nishnaabemwin dialect of the Lake Huron shore and Manitoulin, is under real strain, and the 21 nations are working together to bring it back.</p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <h2>Where it stands</h2>
  <p>In the 2021 Census, about 1,160 people in Robinson Huron Treaty territory could speak the language, and only about 545 spoke it at home. Across the country, the number of Ojibway-language speakers fell more than 5 percent between 2016 and 2021, and many people carry the language as a mother tongue without being able to hold a conversation in it. These are small numbers, and they are the reason the work is urgent.</p>

  <h2>What is being done</h2>
  <p>The 21 Robinson Huron Treaty nations are building a shared Anishinaabemowin reclamation strategy, funded by interest from the annuities settlement, reported at about $16 million over three years. It is one of the most hopeful things to come out of the settlement: the nations choosing, together, to put treaty money toward the language. Local institutions carry this work too, including the Ojibwe Cultural Foundation in M'Chigeeng, which has been a language hub since 1974 and runs its own Ojibwe-language radio, and Kenjgewin Teg.</p>

  <h2>On this site</h2>
  <p>We use Anishinaabemowin in our own dialect where we can, drawing first on local and community sources and on the Nishnaabemwin Online Dictionary of the Lake Huron and Manitoulin language. Our word list grows over time, and Elders and language keepers guide it. We never invent or machine-translate a word; where nothing sourced exists, we leave the English. If you see something we can say better, tell us.</p>

  <h2>Look up a word</h2>
  <p>Search a word in English or Anishinaabemowin. Results come from the Sagamok community corpus, with the source and community attribution shown. This is a small, growing word list, so a search may find nothing yet.</p>

  <form class="lex" method="get" action="/treaty/language" role="search">
    <label class="lex__label" for="lex-q">Look up a word in Anishinaabemowin</label>
    <div class="lex__row">
      <input type="text" id="lex-q" name="q" value="{{ lookup.q|default('') }}"
             placeholder="e.g. spoon" autocomplete="off" maxlength="120" aria-label="Word to look up">
      <button type="submit">Look up</button>
    </div>
    <p class="lex__note">Words are served from the Sagamok community corpus. We never machine-translate or invent a word.</p>
  </form>

  {% if lookup.performed %}
    {% set result = lookup.result %}
    {% if not result.available %}
      <div class="notice notice--caveat" role="status">
        <p>The word lookup is temporarily unavailable. Please try again in a little while.</p>
      </div>
    {% elseif not result.hasMatches %}
      <div class="notice" role="status">
        <p>No sourced word found for <strong>{{ lookup.q }}</strong> yet. Our community word list is small and grows over time, so it may be added later.</p>
      </div>
    {% else %}
      <p class="muted">Found {{ result.count }} {{ result.count == 1 ? 'entry' : 'entries' }} for <strong>{{ lookup.q }}</strong>.</p>
      {% for match in result.matches %}
        <div class="lex-entry">
          <p class="lex-entry__word" lang="oj">{{ match.word }}</p>
          {% if match.definitions is not empty %}
            <p class="lex-entry__def">{{ match.definitions|join('; ') }}</p>
          {% endif %}
          <dl class="lex-entry__meta">
            {% if match.label %}
              <dt>Dialect</dt>
              <dd>{{ match.label }}{% if match.dialect and match.dialect not in match.label %} ({{ match.dialect }}){% endif %}</dd>
            {% endif %}
            {% if match.attribution %}
              <dt>Attribution</dt>
              <dd>{{ match.attribution }}{% if match.attributionSource %} ({{ match.attributionSource }}){% endif %}</dd>
            {% endif %}
            {% if match.sourceUrl %}
              <dt>Source</dt>
              <dd><a href="{{ match.sourceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View the community source</a></dd>
            {% endif %}
          </dl>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% if result.usage %}
        <p class="lex-usage">
          This content is community-governed{% if result.usage.governance %} under {{ result.usage.governance }}{% endif %} and shared on noncommercial terms. It is provided by the Sagamok community and shown here with attribution; its appearance here does not imply any endorsement.{% if result.usage.referenceUrl %} <a href="{{ result.usage.referenceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Reference</a>.{% endif %}
        </p>
      {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Sources</h2>
  <ul class="src-links">
    <li><a href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/sudbury/language-anishinaabemowin-revitalization-strategy-9.7238935" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CBC, on the RHT 21-nation Anishinaabemowin reclamation strategy and the 1,160-speaker figure</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www150.statcan.gc.ca/n1/daily-quotidien/220921/dq220921a-eng.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Statistics Canada, 2021 Census of Indigenous languages</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://dictionary.nishnaabemwin.atlas-ling.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nishnaabemwin Online Dictionary (Odawa and Eastern Ojibwe, Lake Huron)</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://www.uccmm.ca/ojibwe-cultural-foundation.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ojibwe Cultural Foundation (UCCMM)</a></li>
  </ul>

  <div class="card card--coral">
    <p class="muted">A member-compiled summary. Figures are point-in-time; verify before relying on them. If you can <a href="/about#corrections">show us an inaccuracy</a>, we will correct it.</p>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
